y |publisher = Scheitlin und Zollikofer | volume = Vol. 3 | year = 1849 }}\n* {{cite book |url=https://books.google.de/books?id=c7LxaLP5xogC |title=The Origin and Diversification of Language |last=Swadesh |first=Morris |date=1971 |publisher=Transaction Publishers  |isbn=978-0-20-236982-2 |language=en}}\n\n{{refend}}\n\n== External links ==\n{{Sister project links |wikt=Category:German language\n|commons=Category:German language\n|b=Category:German language\n|n=no\n|q=German proverbs\n|s=no\n|v=Topic:German\n|voy=German phrasebook\n|species=no\n|d=Q188\n|mw=no\n|m=no\n}}\n{{WikisourceWiki|code=de}}\n{{InterWiki|code=de}}\n* {{Wikisource-inline|list=\n** {{Cite EB1911|wstitle=German Language |short=x |noicon=x}}\n** [[Mark Twain]], [[s:The Awful German Language|The Awful German Language]], 1880\n** [[Carl Schurz]], [[s:The German Mothertongue|The German Mothertongue]], 1897\n** {{Cite AmCyc|wstitle=Germany, Language and Literature of |short=x |noicon=x}}\n}}\n* {{dmoz|Science/Social_Sciences/Linguistics/Languages/Natural/Indo-European/Germanic/German|German (language)}}\n* [http://www.duden.de/ Duden, Germany's top-selling dictionary]\n* [http://dict.leo.org/ende/index_en.html Leo, free online German dictionary]\n* [https://archive.org/details/VerbreitungDerDeutschenSprache Dissemination of the German language in Europe around 1913 (map, 300 dpi)]\n<!-- ======================== {{No more links}} ============================\n    | PLEASE BE CAUTIOUS IN ADDING MORE LINKS TO THIS ARTICLE. Wikipedia  |\n    | is not a collection of links nor should it be used for advertising. |\n    |                                                                     |\n    |           Excessive or inappropriate links WILL BE DELETED.         |\n    | See [[Wikipedia:External links]] & [[Wikipedia:Spam]] for details.  |\n    |                                                                     |\n    | If there are already plentiful links, please propose additions or   |\n    | replacem